Track changes with a version number in the README.md file with the major.minor.patch format. 
List all the mcp servers used to create this project and the tools, include the mcp server setup in the readme, you are using in the readme.

Always update the README.md file with any changes made to the codebase.

Create a CHANGES.md file to document changes between versions.

Add new feature requests/changes to the TODO.md file.

Strikethrough items from the TODO.md list that are done, include the version number.

Push changes to the repository when things are working nicely, tag the release. Increment the versioning with every repo push. Version rules: major.minor.patch Major: goes up when there is a breaking change, minor: goes up when there is a new feature, patch: goes up when there is a bug fix.
